This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) because it deals with the evaluative character of words and their semantic orientation. It also involves using a Web search engine to analyze the results, which is a common technique in natural language processing. 

It could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category because the method involves querying a search engine and analyzing the results. 

The paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category because it introduces an algorithm for unsupervised learning of semantic orientation. 

The artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility because the paper involves developing an algorithm for analyzing language and making predictions about the desirability of words. 

Finally, the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category may be relevant because the paper deals with the analysis of language and the development of algorithms for understanding and processing it.
